        <section id="faqs">
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>1. What is Core?</h3>
            <p>
              Core is a social media platform created exclusively for software
              engineers (SWEs) to connect, collaborate, and share their projects
              and posts within specialized communities.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>2. How can I join Core?</h3>
            <p>
              You can join Core by signing up for an account using your email
              address or by linking your existing GitHub or LinkedIn profile.
              Simply follow the registration process on our homepage.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>3. Is Core free to use?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes, Core offers a free basic membership that allows you to access
              most features. However, we also offer premium membership options
              with additional benefits.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>4. What are communities on Core?</h3>
            <p>
              Communities on Core are groups of like-minded software engineers
              who share common interests, technologies, or projects. You can
              join communities to engage in discussions and share your work.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>5. How do I create a post in a community?</h3>
            <p>
              To create a post, navigate to the community you want to post in,
              click the "Create Post" button, and fill in the details, including
              text, images, and links. You can also choose whether to make your
              post public or restricted to community members.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>6. Can I follow communities and users on Core?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes, you can follow both communities and individual users. This
              allows you to stay updated on the latest posts and discussions
              from your favorite communities and users.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>7. How do I control the privacy of my posts?</h3>
            <p>
              When creating a post, you can choose its privacy settings. You can
              make a post public, visible to your followers, or restricted to a
              specific community. You can also set individual privacy
              preferences for your profile.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>8. What safety measures does Core have in place?</h3>
            <p>
              Core takes safety seriously. We have robust reporting and blocking
              features to help you report and block abusive or inappropriate
              content or users. Our community guidelines promote a positive and
              respectful environment.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>9. How can I change my password on Core?</h3>
            <p>
              You can change your password by going to your account settings,
              selecting the "Security" section, and following the instructions
              to update your password.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>10. Can I customize my Core profile?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes, you can customize your Core profile by adding a profile
              picture, a bio, and links to your GitHub and LinkedIn profiles.
              This helps other users learn more about you.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>11. How can I contact Core's support team for assistance?</h3>
            <p>
              You can reach out to our support team by sending an email to
              <a href="mailto:support@coreplatform.com"
                >support@coreplatform.com</a
              >
              or by using the live chat support available during business hours.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>
              12. What is the typical response time for support inquiries?
            </h3>
            <p>
              Our support team aims to respond to inquiries within 24 hours.
              However, response times may vary based on the volume of requests.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>13. Does Core have a mobile app?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes, we offer official mobile apps for both iOS and Android
              devices. You can download them from the App Store and Google Play
              Store.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>14. How do I troubleshoot issues with the Core mobile app?</h3>
            <p>
              If you encounter issues with the mobile app, you can refer to our
              mobile app troubleshooting guide available in the Help section of
              the app. You can also contact support for assistance.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>15. Does Core support multiple languages?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes, we aim to provide support in multiple languages to
              accommodate our global user base. You can select your preferred
              language in your account settings.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>
              16. Are there specialized communities for different regions or
              tech stacks?
            </h3>
            <p>
              Yes, we have communities tailored to different regions and tech
              stacks to ensure that users can connect with others who share
              their interests and expertise.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>
              17. How can I provide feedback or suggest improvements for Core?
            </h3>
            <p>
              We encourage you to share your feedback and suggestions through
              the "Feedback and Suggestions" section on our platform. Your input
              is valuable in helping us enhance the Core experience.
            </p>
          </div>
